#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:5
msgid "How to write a NumPy how-to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:7
msgid "How-tos get straight to the point -- they"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:9
msgid "answer a focused question, or"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:10
msgid ""
"narrow a broad question into focused questions that the user can choose "
"among."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:15
msgid "A stranger has asked for directions..."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:17
msgid "**\"I need to refuel my car.\"**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:21
msgid "Give a brief but explicit answer"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:23
msgid ""
"*\"Three kilometers/miles, take a right at Hayseed Road, it's on your left."
"\"*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:25
msgid ""
"Add helpful details for newcomers (\"Hayseed Road\", even though it's the "
"only turnoff at three km/mi). But not irrelevant ones:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:28
msgid "Don't also give directions from Route 7."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:29
msgid "Don't explain why the town has only one filling station."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:31
msgid ""
"If there's related background (tutorial, explanation, reference, alternative "
"approach), bring it to the user's attention with a link (\"Directions from "
"Route 7,\" \"Why so few filling stations?\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:38
msgid "Delegate"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:40
msgid "*\"Three km/mi, take a right at Hayseed Road, follow the signs.\"*"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:42
msgid ""
"If the information is already documented and succinct enough for a how-to, "
"just link to it, possibly after an introduction (\"Three km/mi, take a "
"right\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:47
msgid "If the question is broad, narrow and redirect it"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:49
msgid "**\"I want to see the sights.\"**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:51
msgid "The *See the sights* how-to should link to a set of narrower how-tos:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:53
msgid "Find historic buildings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:54
msgid "Find scenic lookouts"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:55
msgid "Find the town center"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:57
msgid ""
"and these might in turn link to still narrower how-tos -- so the town center "
"page might link to"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:60
msgid "Find the court house"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:61
msgid "Find city hall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:63
msgid ""
"By organizing how-tos this way, you not only display the options for people "
"who need to narrow their question, you also have provided answers for users "
"who start with narrower questions (\"I want to see historic buildings,\" "
"\"Which way to city hall?\")."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:70
msgid "If there are many steps, break them up"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:72
msgid "If a how-to has many steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:74
msgid ""
"Consider breaking a step out into an individual how-to and linking to it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:75
msgid ""
"Include subheadings. They help readers grasp what's coming and return where "
"they left off."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:80
msgid "Why write how-tos when there's Stack Overflow, Reddit, Gitter...?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:82
msgid "We have authoritative answers."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:83
msgid "How-tos make the site less forbidding to non-experts."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:84
msgid ""
"How-tos bring people into the site and help them discover other information "
"that's here ."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:86
msgid "Creating how-tos helps us see NumPy usability through new eyes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:90
msgid "Aren't how-tos and tutorials the same thing?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:92
msgid ""
"People use the terms \"how-to\" and \"tutorial\" interchangeably, but we "
"draw a distinction, following Daniele Procida's `taxonomy of documentation`_."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:97
msgid ""
"Documentation needs to meet users where they are.  *How-tos* offer get-it-"
"done information; the user wants steps to copy and doesn't necessarily want "
"to understand NumPy. *Tutorials* are warm-fuzzy information; the user wants "
"a feel for some aspect of NumPy (and again, may or may not care about deeper "
"knowledge)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:103
msgid ""
"We distinguish both tutorials and how-tos from *Explanations*, which are "
"deep dives intended to give understanding rather than immediate assistance, "
"and *References*, which give complete, authoritative data on some concrete "
"part of NumPy (like its API) but aren't obligated to paint a broader picture."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:108
msgid "For more on tutorials, see :doc:`numpy-tutorials:tutorial-style-guide`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:112
msgid "Is this page an example of a how-to?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../user/how-to-how-to.rst:114
msgid ""
"Yes -- until the sections with question-mark headings; they explain rather "
"than giving directions. In a how-to, those would be links."
msgstr ""
